data.meta_description:
8 likes, 2 comments - raydiotwins on March 26, 2022: "Black WOMEN History...
Sarah Vaughan was born on March 27, 1924, in Newark, New Jersey. Sarah Vaughan grew up with a love of music and performing. Winning a talent competition held at Harlem's Apollo Theater launched her singing career. She worked with bandleaders Earl Hines and Billy Eckstine before becoming a successful solo performer who commingled pop and jazz. At age 66, Vaughan died in Hidden Hills, California, on April 3, 1990.
